automenta.vivisect.dimensionalize

Class HyperassociativeMap<N,E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • automenta.vivisect.dimensionalize.HyperassociativeMap<N,E>
  • Type Parameters:
    N - The node type

    public class HyperassociativeMap<N,E>
extends Object
    FROM: http://gitlab.syncleus.com/syncleus/dANN-core/raw/v2.x/src/main/java/com/syncleus/dann/graph/drawing/hyperassociativemap/HyperassociativeMap.java A Hyperassociative Map is a new type of algorithm that organizes an arbitrary graph of interconnected nodes according to its associations to other nodes. Once a new Hyperassociative Map has been associated and aligned, nodes that are most closely associated will be closest to each other. For more info, please see the Hyperassociative-Map dANN Wiki page.
    Author:
    Jeffrey Phillips Freeman
